ove Crime|Crime d'amour]]'' (2010)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Point of No Return (1993 film)|Point of No Return]]'' (1993)\n| ''[[La Femme Nikita (film)|La Femme Nikita]]'' (1990)\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Port of Seven Seas]]'' (1938)\n| ''[[Marius (1931 film)|Marius]]'' (1929)<br>''[[Fanny (1932 film)|Fanny]]'' (1932)<br>''[[C\u00e9sar (film)|C\u00e9sar]]'' (1936)\n| \n|-\n| ''[[The Postman Always Rings Twice (1946 film)|The Postman Always Rings Twice]]'' (1946)\n| ''[[Le Dernier Tournant]]'' (1939)\n| The novel ''The Postman Always Rings Twice'' ([[James M. Cain]])\n|-\n| ''[[The Postman Always Rings Twice (1981 film)|The Postman Always Rings Twice]]'' (1981)\n| ''[[Le Dernier Tournant]]'' (1939)\n| The novel ''The Postman Always Rings Twice'' ([[James M. Cain]])\n|-\n| ''[[Pure Luck]]'' (1991)\n| ''[[La Ch\u00e8vre]]'' (1981)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Quick Change]]'' (1990)\n| ''[[Hold-Up (1985 film)|Hold-Up]]'' (1985)\n| The novel ''Quick Change'' ([[Jay Cronley]])\n|-\n| ''[[The Rebel Son]]'' (1938)\n| ''[[Taras Bulba (1936 film)|Taras Bulba]]'' (1936)\n| The novel ''[[Taras Bulba]]'' ([[Nikolai Gogol]])\n|-\n| ''[[Reflections of Murder]]'' (1974, TV film)\n| ''[[Les Diaboliques (film)|Les Diaboliques]]'' (1955)\n| The novel ''Celle qui n'\u00e9tait plus'' ([[Boileau-Narcejac]])\n|-\n| ''[[Return to Paradise (1998 film)|Return to Paradise]]'' (1998)\n| ''Force majeure'' (1989)\n| \n|-\n| ''Rigged'' (1985)\n| ''{{Interlanguage link multi|D\u00e9lit de fuite|fr|3=D\u00e9lit de fuite (film, 1959)|lt=D\u00e9lit de fuite}}'' (1959)\n| The novel ''Hit and Run'' ([[James Hadley Chase]])\n|-\n| ''[[Rough Magic]]'' (1995)\n| ''[[Une blonde comme \u00e7a]]'' (1962)\n| The novel ''Miss Shumway Waves a Wand'' ([[James Hadley Chase]])\n|-\n| ''[[Scarlet Street]]'' (1945)\n| ''[[La Chienne]]'' (1931)\n| The novel ''La Chienne'' (Georges de La Fouchardi\u00e8re)\n|-\n| ''[[Second Bureau (1936 film)|Second Bureau]]'' (1936)\n| ''[[Second Bureau (1935 film)|Deuxi\u00e8me bureau]]'' (1935)\n| The novel ''Second 