 Countess of Monte Cristo (1934 film)|The Countess of Monte Cristo]]'' (1934)\n| ''[[The Countess of Monte Cristo (1932 film)|The Countess of Monte Cristo]]'' (1932)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Countess of Monte Cristo (1948 film)|The Countess of Monte Cristo]]'' (1948)\n| ''[[The Countess of Monte Cristo (1932 film)|The Countess of Monte Cristo]]'' (1932)\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Desire (1936 film)|Desire]]'' (1936)\n| ''[[Happy Days in Aranjuez]]'' (1933)\n| The play ''Die sch\u00f6nen Tage von Aranjuez'' ([[J\u00e1nos Sz\u00e9kely (writer)|J\u00e1nos Sz\u00e9kely]], [[Robert A. Stemmle]])\n|-\n| ''[[The Diplomatic Lover]]'' (1934)\n| ''[[The Ladies Diplomat]]'' (1932)\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Doomed Battalion]]'' (1932)\n| ''[[Mountains on Fire]]'' (1931)\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Dreaming Lips (1937 film)|Dreaming Lips]]'' (1937)\n| ''[[Dreaming Lips (1932 film)|Dreaming Lips]]'' (1932)\n| The play ''[[M\u00e9lo]]'' ([[Henri Bernstein]])\n|-\n| ''[[Dreams Come True (1936 film)|Dreams Come True]]'' (1936)\n| ''[[The World's in Love]]'' (1935, Austria)\n| The operetta ''Clo-Clo'' ([[Franz Lehar]], [[Bela Jenbach]])\n|-\n| ''[[Eight Girls in a Boat (1934 film)|Eight Girls in a Boat]]'' (1934)\n| ''[[Eight Girls in a Boat (1932 film)|Eight Girls in a Boat]]'' (1932)\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Emil and the Detectives (1935 film)|Emil and the Detectives]]'' (1935)\n| ''[[Emil and the Detectives (1931 film)|Emil and the Detectives]]'' (1931)\n| The novel ''[[Emil and the Detectives]]'' ([[Erich K\u00e4stner]])\n|-\n| ''[[Emil and the Detectives (1964 film)|Emil and the Detectives]]'' (1964)\n| ''[[Emil and the Detectives (1931 film)|Emil and the Detectives]]'' (1931)\n| The novel ''[[Emil and the Detectives]]'' ([[Erich K\u00e4stner]])\n|-\n| ''[[The Emperor's Candlesticks (film)|The Emperor's Candlesticks]]'' (1937)\n| ''[[The Emperor's Candlesticks (1936 film)|The Emperor's Candlesticks]]'' (1936, Austria)\n| The novel ''[[The Emperor's Candlesticks]]'' ([[Baroness Orczy]])\n|-\n| ''[[Escapade (1935 film)|Escapade]]'' (