uation-and-case-numbers].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Cumulative confirmed cases by State, Territory & Nationally<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":43\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.health.gov.au/news/health-alerts/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov-health-alert/coronavirus-covid-19-current-situation-and-case-numbers|title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) current situation and case numbers|last=|first=|date=17 March 2020|website=Australian Government Department of Health|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317013820/https://www.health.gov.au/news/health-alerts/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov-health-alert/coronavirus-covid-19-current-situation-and-case-numbers|archive-date=17 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n!\n!colspan=|{{nowrap|[[New South Wales|NSW]]<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 media releases from NSW Health |url=https://www.health.nsw.gov.au/news/Pages/2020-nsw-health.aspx |publisher=NSW Health |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>{{Efn|Since 5 March, the figures in this column also include a Northern Territory case diagnosed on 4 March, which has been counted as a NSW case by NSW Health from 5 March after the case returned to his home state.<ref name=\"health.nsw.gov.au\" />|name=|group=}}}}\n!colspan=|[[Queensland|QLD]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Current status and contact tracing alerts \u2014 coronavirus (COVID-19) |url=https://www.qld.gov.au/health/conditions/health-alerts/coronavirus-covid-19/current-status/current-status-and-contact-tracing-alerts |publisher=QLD Government |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n!colspan=|[[Victoria (Australia)|VIC]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhhs.vic.gov.au/coronavirus|title=Department of Health and Human Services Victoria {{!}} Coronavirus disease (COVID-19)|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Department of Health and Human Services Victoria|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n!colspan=|[[South Australia|SA]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Confirmed and suspected cases of 